r is 3 inches. Laid end-to-end, how long?","o":["4 inches","9 inches","10 inches","11 inches"],"a":2,"e":"7 + 3 = 10 inches.","d":"m"},{"t":"A desk is 36 inches long. A shelf is 24 inches. How much longer is the desk?","o":["10 inches","12 inches","14 inches","60 inches"],"a":1,"e":"36 − 24 = 12 inches longer.","d":"m"},{"t":"A ribbon is 48 inches. You cut off 19 inches. How much is left?","o":["27 inches","29 inches","31 inches","39 inches"],"a":1,"e":"48 − 19 = 29 inches. Regroup: 8<9, regroup 1 ten → 18−9=9.","d":"h"},{"t":"A pencil is about how many inches long?","o":["7 inches","70 inches","1 inch","100 inches"],"a":0,"e":"A pencil is about 7 inches long. 70 or 100 inches would be way too big!","d":"e"},{"t":"A crayon is about how many inches long?","o":["30 inches","4 inches","40 inches","1 foot"],"a":1,"e":"A crayon is about 4 inches long. It fits in your hand, so it is small!","d":"e"},{"t":"A paper clip is about how many inches long?","o":["1 inch","10 inches","5 inches","12 inches"],"a":0,"e":"A paper clip is tiny! It is about 1 inch long.","d":"e"},{"t":"A ruler is how many inches long?","o":["6 inches","10 inches","12 inches","20 inches"],"a":2,"e":"A ruler is 12 inches long. That is the same as 1 foot!","d":"e"},{"t":"Your shoe is about how many inches long?","o":["2 inches","8 inches","30 inches","50 inches"],"a":1,"e":"Your shoe is about 8 inches long. That is a little less than a ruler!","d":"e"},{"t":"A door is about how many feet tall?","o":["2 feet","7 feet","20 feet","70 feet"],"a":1,"e":"A door is about 7 feet tall. That is taller than most grown-ups!","d":"e"},{"t":"A spoon is about how many inches long?","o":["6 inches","60 inches","1 inch","30 inches"],"a":0,"e":"A spoon is about 6 inches long. It fits in your hand!","d":"e"},{"t":"A baseball bat is about how many feet long?","o":["1 foot","10 feet","3 feet","30 feet"],"a":2,"e":"A baseball bat is about 3 feet long. That is the same as 36 inches!","d":"e"},{"t":"A bed is about how many feet long?","o":["1 foot","6 feet","60 feet","100 feet"],"a":1,"e":"A bed is about 6 feet long. That is big enough for a grown-up to sleep on!","d":"e"},{"t":"A new eraser is about how many inches long?","o":["2 inches","12 inches","20 inches","8 inches"],"a":0,"e":"A new eraser is about 2 inches long. It is very small!","d":"e"},{"t":"A fork is about how many inches long?","o":["1 inch","50 inches","7 inches","30 inches"],"a":2,"e":"A fork is about 7 inches long. It fits in your hand when you eat!","d":"e"},{"t":"A banana is about how many inches long?","o":["1 inch","30 inches","8 inches","20 inches"],"a":2,"e":"A banana is about 8 inches long. It is a little shorter than a ruler!","d":"e"},{"t":"A marker is about how many inches long?","o":["5 inches","50 inches","1 inch","25 inches"],"a":0,"e":"A marker is about 5 inches long. It is a little bigger than a crayon!","d":"e"},{"t":"A desk is about how many feet wide?","o":["4 feet","40 feet","1 foot","20 feet"],"a":0,"e":"A desk is about 4 feet wide. That is about as long as two rulers!","d":"e"},{"t":"A lunchbox is about how many inches long?","o":["1 inch","50 inches","10 inches","30 inches"],"a":2,"e":"A lunchbox is about 10 inches long. It is a little shorter than a ruler!","d":"e"},{"t":"A toothbrush is about how many inches long?","o":["7 inches","1 inch","20 inches","70 inches"],"a":0,"e":"A toothbrush is about 7 inches long. It fits in your hand when you brush!","d":"e"},{"t":"A car is about how many feet long?","o":["2 feet","15 feet","100 feet","50 feet"],"a":1,"e":"A car is about 15 feet long. That is a lot bigger than you!","d":"e"},{"t":"Your finger is about how many inches long?","o":["10 inches","50 inches","3 inches","30 inches"],"a":2,"e":"Your finger is about 3 inches long. It is small, so the number is small too!","d":"e"},{"t":"A key is about how many inches long?","o":["10 inches","3 inches","30 inches","12 inches"],"a":1,"e":"A key is about 3 inches long. It is small enough to fit in your pocket!","d":"e"},{"t":"A book is about how many inches tall?","o":["1 inch","10 inches","100 inches","50 inches"],"a":1,"e":"A book is about 10 inches tall. That is a little less than a ruler!","d":"e"},{"t":"Would you measure a football field in inches or feet?","o":["Inches","Feet","Paper clips","Crayons"],"a":1,"e":"A football field is very long, so we use feet. Inches would give a huge number!","d":"e"},{"t":"Would you measure a ladybug in inches or feet?","o":["Feet","Inches","Yards","Meters"],"a":1,"e":"A ladybug is very tiny! We measure small things in inches.","d":"e"},{"t":"A rope is 12 inches long. You need 20 inches total. How many more inches do you need?","o":["6 inches","8 inches","10 inches","32 inches"],"a":1,"e":"20 - 12 = 8. You need 8 more inches to make 20 inches.","d":"m"},{"t":"Which is longer: a 10-inch string or a 1-foot string?","o":["The 10-inch string","The 1-foot string","They are the same","Cannot tell"],"a":1,"e":"1 foot = 12 inches. Since 12 > 10, the 1-foot string is longer!","d":"m"},{"t":"A ribbon is 9 inches long. A second ribbon is 5 inches long. How much longer is the first ribbon?","o":["14 inches","3 inches","4 inches","5 inches"],"a":2,"e":"9 - 5 = 4 inches. The first ribbon is 4 inches longer.","d":"m"},{"t":"Would you measure a swimming pool in inches or feet?","o":["Inches","Feet","Paper clips","Erasers"],"a":1,"e":"A swimming pool is very big! We use feet to measure big things.","d":"m"},{"t":"Ben has a string that is 7 inches long. He adds 6 more inches. How long is it now?","o":["1 inch","12 inches","13 inches","76 inches"],"a":2,"e":"7 + 6 = 13 inches. The string is now 13 inches long.","d":"h"},{"t":"Would you measure a pencil in centimeters or meters?","o":["Meters","Centimeters","Feet","Yards"],"a":1,"e":"A pencil is small, so we use centimeters. Meters are for bigger things!","d":"m"},{"t":"A stick is 15 inches. A straw is 8 inches. How much shorter is the straw?","o":["7 inches","23 inches","8 inches","6 inches"],"a":0,"e":"15 - 8 = 7 inches. The straw is 7 inches shorter than the stick.","d":"m"},{"t":"Which unit would you use to measure the length of your classroom?","o":["Inches","Centimeters","Feet","Paper clips"],"a":2,"e":"A classroom is big! We use feet to measure big spaces.","d":"m"},{"t":"A paintbrush is a little shorter than a ruler. About how many inches long is it?","o":["2 inches","10 inches","30 inches","50 inches"],"a":1,"e":"A ruler is 12 inches. A little shorter would be about 10 inches.","d":"m"},{"t":"Maya's pencil is 6 inches. Her marker is 5 inches. How many inches are they together?","o":["1 inch","11 inches","30 inches","56 inches"],"a":1,"e":"6 + 5 = 11 inches. Together they measure 11 inches.","d":"m"},{"t":"Would you measure a park bench in inches or feet?","o":["Inches","Feet","Centimeters","Paper clips"],"a":1,"e":"A park bench is big! We use feet to measure things that are several feet long.","d":"m"},{"t":"A tape is 14 inches long. You cut off 6 inches. How much tape is left?","o":["8 inches","20 inches","6 inches","9 inches"],"a":0,"e":"14 - 6 = 8 inches. You have 8 inches of tape left.","d":"h"},{"t":"Which is shorter: a 2-foot table or a 30-inch table?","o":["The 2-foot table","The 30-inch table","They are the same","Cannot tell"],"a":0,"e":"2 feet = 24 inches. Since 24 < 30, the 2-foot table is shorter!","d":"m"},{"t":"Liam needs 18 inches of ribbon. He has 11 inches. How many more inches does he need?","o":["29 inches","7 inches","8 inches","6 inches"],"a":1,"e":"18 - 11 = 7 inches. Liam needs 7 more inches of ribbon.","d":"h"},{"t":"Would you measure a caterpillar in centimeters or meters?","o":["Meters","Centimeters","Feet","Yards"],"a":1,"e":"A caterpillar is very small! We use centimeters for small things.","d":"m"},{"t":"A crayon is 4 inches and a pen is 6 inches. Which is longer and by how much?","o":["Crayon, by 2 inches","Pen, by 2 inches","Pen, by 10 inches","They are the same"],"a":1,"e":"6 - 4 = 2. The pen is 2 inches longer than the crayon.","d":"m"},{"t":"A piece of yarn is some inches long. You need 5 more inches to reach 16 inches. How long is the yarn?","o":["21 inches","11 inches","5 inches","10 inches"],"a":1,"e":"16 - 5 = 11 inches. The yarn is 11 inches long.","d":"m"},{"t":"Would you measure the length of a school bus in inches or feet?","o":["Inches","Feet","Centimeters","Millimeters"],"a":1,"e":"A school bus is very long! We use feet for big things like buses.","d":"m"},{"t":"Sam's ribbon is 15 inches. He cuts off 7 inches, then cuts 3 more inches. How long is it now?","o":["5 inches","8 inches","10 inches","25 inches"],"a":0,"e":"15 - 7 = 8, then 8 - 3 = 5 inches. Two cuts means two subtractions!","d":"h"},{"t":"Jenna says a door is 7 inches tall. Is this reasonable?","o":["Yes, that sounds right","No, a door is about 7 feet tall","No, a door is 2 inches tall","Yes, doors are small"],"a":1,"e":"7 inches is only about the length of a pencil. A door is about 7 feet tall, not 7 inches!","d":"m"},{"t":"A string is 20 inches. Mia uses 8 inches for a bracelet and 6 inches for a ring. How much is left?","o":["6 inches","14 inches","34 inches","8 inches"],"a":0,"e":"20 - 8 = 12, then 12 - 6 = 6 inches left. She used 14 inches total.","d":"h"},{"t":"Tom says his eraser is 2 feet long. What did Tom do wrong?","o":["He used the wrong unit — an eraser is about 2 inches","He measured correctly","He should have said 2 meters","Erasers cannot be measured"],"a":0,"e":"2 feet = 24 inches! An eraser is only about 2 inches long. Tom confused feet with inches.","d":"h"},{"t":"A board is 3 feet long. How many inches is that?","o":["3 inches","24 inches","36 inches","30 inches"],"a":2,"e":"1 foot = 12 inches. So 3 feet = 3 x 12 = 36 inches.","d":"m"},{"t":"Kai has a rope that is 2 feet long. He needs 30 inches total. How many more inches does he need?","o":["6 inches","28 inches","10 inches","12 inches"],"a":0,"e":"2 feet = 24 inches. 30 - 24 = 6 more inches needed.","d":"h"},{"t":"Lily says a car is 15 inches long. Does that make sense?","o":["Yes, cars are small","No, a car is about 15 feet long","Yes, that is correct","No, a car is 1 inch long"],"a":1,"e":"15 inches is about the length of a big book. A car is about 15 feet long, not 15 inches!","d":"m"},{"t":"Jake measures a table as 4 feet. Emma measures the same table as 50 inches. Who is closer to correct?","o":["Jake","Emma","They are both wrong","They are both right"],"a":1,"e":"4 feet = 48 inches. A table is about 48-50 inches, so Emma's 50 inches is very close!","d":"h"},{"t":"A wire is 18 inches. You cut off 5 inches, then add a 9-inch piece. How long is the wire now?","o":["22 inches","4 inches","14 inches","32 inches"],"a":0,"e":"18 - 5 = 13, then 13 + 9 = 22 inches. Subtract first, then add!","d":"h"},{"t":"Noah says a football field is 100 inches long. What mistake did he make?","o":["He said inches instead of yards","He counted wrong","He is correct","He should have said 100 centimeters"],"a":0,"e":"100 inches is only about 8 feet! A football field is about 100 yards (300 feet). Noah used the wrong unit.","d":"h"},{"t":"Amy has 3 pieces of tape: 6 inches, 4 inches, and 7 inches. How many inches of tape does she have in all?","o":["17 inches","11 inches","10 inches","15 inches"],"a":0,"e":"6 + 4 + 7 = 17 inches of tape in all.","d":"h"},{"t":"A pipe is 2 feet 4 inches long. How many inches is that in all?","o":["24 inches","28 inches","6 inches","34 inches"],"a":1,"e":"2 feet = 24 inches. 24 + 4 = 28 inches total.","d":"m"},{"t":"Which is longer: 2 feet or 20 inches? By how much?","o":["2 feet, by 4 inches","20 inches, by 4 inches","They are the same","2 feet, by 2 inches"],"a":0,"e":"2 feet = 24 inches. 24 - 20 = 4. So 2 feet is 4 inches longer.","d":"m"},{"t":"Carlos says his dad is 6 inches tall. Is that reasonable? Why not?","o":["Yes, grown-ups are 6 inches","No, 6 inches is the size of a spoon — his dad is about 6 feet tall","Yes, that is normal","No, his dad is 60 inches"],"a":1,"e":"6 inches is about the length of a spoon! Carlos meant 6 feet, which is a normal height for a grown-up.","d":"m"},{"t":"A scarf is 4 feet long. Maya cuts it into 2 equal pieces. How many inches is each piece?","o":["2 feet","24 inches","12 inches","48 inches"],"a":1,"e":"4 feet = 48 inches. 48 / 2 = 24 inches each. That is the same as 2 feet!","d":"m"},{"t":"Zoe has 10 inches of string. She needs 3 pieces that are each 4 inches. Does she have enough?","o":["Yes, she has plenty","No, she needs 12 inches but only has 10","Yes, 10 is more than 4","No, she needs 7 inches"],"a":1,"e":"3 pieces x 4 inches = 12 inches needed. She only has 10 inches. She is 2 inches short!","d":"h"},{"t":"A stick is 1 foot 8 inches long. A second stick is 22 inches long. Which is longer?","o":["The first stick","The second stick","They are the same","Cannot tell"],"a":1,"e":"1 foot 8 inches = 12 + 8 = 20 inches. Since 22 > 20, the second stick is longer by 2 inches.","d":"h"},{"t":"Leo measures a book as 30 centimeters. His friend says that is about 12 inches. Is his friend right?","o":["Yes, 30 cm is about 12 inches","No, 30 cm is about 30 inches","No, 30 cm is about 3 inches","Cannot convert"],"a":0,"e":"1 inch is about 2.5 centimeters. 30 / 2.5 = 12. So yes, 30 cm is about 12 inches!","d":"h"},{"t":"Ella has a 24-inch ribbon. She cuts it into 3 equal pieces and gives 1 away. How many inches does she keep?","o":["8 inches","16 inches","12 inches","24 inches"],"a":1,"e":"24 / 3 = 8 inches per piece. She keeps 2 pieces: 2 x 8 = 16 inches.","d":"h"},{"t":"Ryan says a classroom is 30 inches long. What is wrong with his answer?","o":["Nothing, that is correct","He used inches instead of feet — a classroom is about 30 feet long","He should have said 30 centimeters","Classrooms cannot be measured"],"a":1,"e":"30 inches is only 2.5 feet — about the width of a desk! A classroom is about 30 feet long. Ryan used the wrong unit.","d":"h"}],"quiz":[{"t":"A pencil goes from 0 to 7 on a ruler. How long is the pencil?