= 1 gallon\nA gallon is the biggest!","a":"Cup → Pint → Quart → Gallon ✅"},{"c":"#1abc9c","tag":"Weight","p":"Weight units:","s":"16 ounces = 1 pound\nAn apple weighs about 1 pound\nA pencil weighs about 1 ounce","a":"Ounces for light, pounds for heavy ✅"},{"c":"#e74c3c","tag":"Try It! Thermometer","p":"Drag the slider to change the temperature:","s":"<div style=\"text-align:center;padding:4px\"><svg width=\"220\" height=\"300\" viewBox=\"0 0 110 150\" style=\"display:block;margin:0 auto\"><rect x=\"15\" y=\"8\" width=\"10\" height=\"110\" rx=\"5\" fill=\"#e8f4f8\" stroke=\"#aaa\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect id=\"ith-fill\" x=\"16\" y=\"84.3\" width=\"8\" height=\"33.7\" fill=\"#e74c3c\"/><circle cx=\"20\" cy=\"129\" r=\"11\" fill=\"#e74c3c\" stroke=\"#aaa\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><circle cx=\"20\" cy=\"129\" r=\"8\" fill=\"#c0392b\"/><line x1=\"25\" y1=\"15.9\" x2=\"29\" y2=\"15.9\" stroke=\"#e74c3c\" stroke-width=\"1.2\"/><text x=\"31\" y=\"15.9\" dominant-baseline=\"central\" font-size=\"6.5\" fill=\"#e74c3c\" font-weight=\"bold\">212°F  Boiling!</text><line x1=\"25\" y1=\"70.8\" x2=\"29\" y2=\"70.8\" stroke=\"#e67e22\" stroke-width=\"1.2\"/><text x=\"31\" y=\"70.8\" dominant-baseline=\"central\" font-size=\"6.5\" fill=\"#e67e22\" font-weight=\"bold\"> 98°F  Body temp</text><line x1=\"25\" y1=\"84.3\" x2=\"29\" y2=\"84.3\" stroke=\"#27ae60\" stroke-width=\"1.2\"/><text x=\"31\" y=\"84.3\" dominant-baseline=\"central\" font-size=\"6.5\" fill=\"#27ae60\" font-weight=\"bold\"> 70°F  Comfortable</text><line x1=\"25\" y1=\"102.6\" x2=\"29\" y2=\"102.6\" stroke=\"#2980b9\" stroke-width=\"1.2\"/><text x=\"31\" y=\"102.6\" dominant-baseline=\"central\" font-size=\"6.5\" fill=\"#2980b9\" font-weight=\"bold\"> 32°F  Freezing!</text></svg><div id=\"ith-dt\" style=\"font-size:32px;font-weight:bold;color:#27ae60;margin:6px 0\">70°F</div><div id=\"ith-lbl\" style=\"font-size:15px;color:#555;margin-bottom:10px\">Comfortable</div><label style=\"font-size:13px;font-weight:bold;color:#333\">&#127777;&#65039; Temperature<br><input id=\"ith-s\" type=\"range\" min=\"0\" max=\"220\" value=\"70\" style=\"width:200px;margin-top:6px\" oninput=\"(function(){var t=+document.getElementById(&#39;ith-s&#39;).value;var fillH=(t-0)/(220-0)*106;var fillY=118-fillH;var el=document.getElementById(&#39;ith-fill&#39;);el.setAttribute(&#39;y&#39;,fillY);el.setAttribute(&#39;height&#39;,fillH);var dt=document.getElementById(&#39;ith-dt&#39;);dt.textContent=t+&#39;°F&#39;;dt.style.color=t<=32?&#39;#2980b9&#39;:t<=75?&#39;#27ae60&#39;:&#39;#e74c3c&#39;;var lbl=t<=32?&#39;Freezing!&#39;:t<=50?&#39;Cold&#39;:t<=65?&#39;Cool&#39;:t<=75?&#39;Comfortable&#39;:t<=90?&#39;Warm&#39;:t<=105?&#39;Hot!&#39;:&#39;Boiling!&#39;;document.getElementById(&#39;ith-lbl&#39;).textContent=lbl;}).call(this)\"></label></div>","a":"Watch the mercury rise and fall! &#x2705;"}],"practice":[{"q":"Water freezes at what temperature?","a":"32 degrees F","h":"32 degrees Fahrenheit is when water turns to ice!","e":"🧊"},{"q":"2 cups = ?","a":"1 pint","h":"Always remember: 2 cups make 1 pint!","e":"🥛"},{"q":"4 quarts = ?","a":"1 gallon","h":"4 quarts fill up 1 whole gallon!","e":"🪣"}],"qBank":[{"t":"At what temperature in degrees Fahrenheit does water freeze?","o":["32","0","100","212"],"a":0,"e":"32°F.","d":"e"},{"t":"It is 35°F outside. What should you wear?","o":["Shorts","T-shirt","Swimsuit","Heavy coat"],"a":3,"e":"35°F is very cold.","d":"m"},{"t":"2 cups is equal to how many pints?","o":["1 pint","2 pints","1 quart","1 gallon"],"a":0,"e":"2 cups=1 pint.","d":"e"},{"t":"4 quarts is equal to how many gallons?","o":["1 gallon","2 pints","2 gallons","4 cups"],"a":0,"e":"4 quarts=1 gallon.","d":"e"},{"t":"16 ounces is equal to how many pounds?","o":["1 pound","2 pounds","half pound","1 gallon"],"a":0,"e":"16 oz=1 lb.","d":"e"},{"t":"The temperature went from 65°F to 78°F. How many degrees warmer did it get?","o":["10","12","15","13"],"a":3,"e":"78-65=13°.","d":"h"},{"t":"At what temperature in degrees Fahrenheit does water boil?","o":["100","150","200","212"],"a":3,"e":"212°F.","d":"e"},{"t":"It is 90°F outside. What should you wear?","o":["Heavy coat","Rain boots","Snow boots","Light clothes"],"a":3,"e":"90°F is hot!","d":"m"},{"t":"2 pints is equal to how many quarts?","o":["1 quart","2 quarts","1 gallon","4 cups"],"a":0,"e":"2 pints=1 quart.","d":"e"},{"t":"Which holds more liquid: a cup or a quart?","o":["Cup","Quart","Equal","Depends"],"a":1,"e":"Quart > cup. 4 cups=1 quart.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is the normal human body temperature in degrees Fahrenheit?","o":["32°F","70°F","98.6°F","212°F"],"a":2,"e":"98.6°F.","d":"e"},{"t":"4 cups is equal to how many quarts?","o":["1 pint","1 gallon","2 pints","1 quart"],"a":3,"e":"4 cups=2 pints=1 quart.","d":"e"},{"t":"Is a gallon bigger than a quart?","o":["True","False","Same","Depends"],"a":0,"e":"1 gallon=4 quarts. True!","d":"e"},{"t":"What is the freezing temperature on the Fahrenheit scale?","o":["0°F","16°F","32°F","100°F"],"a":2,"e":"32°F.","d":"e"},{"t":"It is 55°F outside. What season is it most likely?","o":["Summer","Winter","Spring or Fall","Very hot day"],"a":2,"e":"55°F is mild — spring or fall.","d":"m"},{"t":"How many pints are in 1 quart?","o":["1","2","3","4"],"a":1,"e":"2 pints=1 quart.","d":"e"},{"t":"Very heavy objects are best measured in which unit?","o":["Cups","Inches","Pounds","Degrees"],"a":2,"e":"Weight in pounds.","d":"e"},{"t":"The temperature went from 70°F to 55°F. How many degrees colder did it get?","o":["10°","12°","15°","20°"],"a":2,"e":"70-55=15°.","d":"h"},{"t":"How many ounces are in 1 pound?","o":["8","12","16","20"],"a":2,"e":"16 oz=1 lb.","d":"e"},{"t":"Which holds more liquid: a cup or a pint?","o":["Cup","Equal","Depends","Pint"],"a":3,"e":"2 cups=1 pint. Pint is bigger.","d":"e"},{"t":"When does the temperature on a thermometer go up?","o":["It gets colder","It gets warmer","It rains","It is dark"],"a":1,"e":"Temperature rises when it gets warmer.","d":"e"},{"t":"Light objects are best measured in which unit?","o":["Pounds","Gallons","Ounces","Feet"],"a":2,"e":"Light things in ounces.","d":"e"},{"t":"4 gallons is equal to how many quarts?","o":["4","8","12","16"],"a":3,"e":"4 gallons × 4 quarts = 16 quarts.","d":"e"},{"t":"It is snowing outside. What is the temperature most likely?","o":["50°F","75°F","32°F or below","100°F"],"a":2,"e":"Snow forms below 32°F.","d":"e"},{"t":"About how much does an apple weigh?","o":["1 ounce","1 pound","1 gallon","1 cup"],"a":1,"e":"An apple ≈ 1 pound.","d":"e"},{"t":"About how much does a pencil weigh?","o":["1 ounce","1 pound","1 ton","10 lbs"],"a":0,"e":"A pencil ≈ 1 ounce.","d":"e"},{"t":"Which of these temperatures is the coldest: 45°F, 32°F, 60°F, or 15°F?","o":["45°F","32°F","60°F","15°F"],"a":3,"e":"15°F is coldest.","d":"h"},{"t":"How many gallons are in 8 quarts?","o":["1","2","3","4"],"a":1,"e":"8÷4=2 gallons.","d":"e"},{"t":"8 pints is equal to how many quarts?","o":["2","4","6","8"],"a":1,"e":"8÷2=4 quarts.","d":"e"},{"t":"What temperature scale is used in the United States?","o":["Celsius","Fahrenheit","Kelvin","Both"],"a":1,"e":"USA uses Fahrenheit.","d":"e"},{"t":"A shape is covered by 4 square units. What is its area?","o":["2 square units","3 square units","4 square units","5 square units"],"a":2,"e":"Count each square inside the shape. There are 4, so the area is 4 square units!","d":"e"},{"t":"A shape is covered by 7 square units. What is its area?","o":["7 square units","6 square units","8 square units","5 square units"],"a":0,"e":"Count each square inside the shape. There are 7, so the area is 7 square units!","d":"m"},{"t":"A shape is covered by 10 square units. What is its area?","o":["8 square units","9 square units","11 square units","10 square units"],"a":3,"e":"Count each square. There are 10 squares, so the area is 10 square units!","d":"m"},{"t":"A shape is covered by 3 square units. What is its area?","o":["3 square units","4 square units","2 square units","6 square units"],"a":0,"e":"There are 3 squares inside the shape. The area is 3 square units!","d":"e"},{"t":"A shape is covered by 6 square units. What is its area?","o":["5 square units","7 square units","6 square units","8 square units"],"a":2,"e":"Count each square inside the shape. There are 6, so the area is 6 square units!","d":"m"},{"t":"A shape is covered by 1 square unit. What is its area?","o":["0 square units","1 square unit","2 square units","3 square units"],"a":1,"e":"There is 1 square inside the shape. The area is 1 square unit!","d":"e"},{"t":"A shape is covered by 9 square units. What is its area?","o":["8 square units","10 square units","9 square units","7 square units"],"a":2,"e":"Count each square. There are 9 squares, so the area is 9 square units!","d":"m"},{"t":"A shape is covered by 5 square units. What is its area?","o":["4 square units","5 square units","6 square units","3 square units"],"a":1,"e":"Count each square inside the shape. There are 5, so the area is 5 square units!","d":"e"},{"t":"A shape is covered by 12 square units. What is its area?","o":["10 square units","11 square units","12 square units","13 square units"],"a":2,"e":"Count each square. There are 12 squares, so the area is 12 square units!","d":"m"},{"t":"A shape is covered by 2 square units. What is its area?","o":["1 square unit","2 square units","3 square units","4 square units"],"a":1,"e":"There are 2 squares inside the shape. The area is 2 square units!","d":"e"},{"t":"A shape is covered by 8 square units. What is its area?","o":["8 square units","6 square units","10 square units","7 square units"],"a":0,"e":"Count each square. There are 8 squares, so the area is 8 square units!","d":"m"},{"t":"A shape is covered by 15 square units. What is its area?","o":["14 square units","16 square units","15 square units","13 square units"],"a":2,"e":"Count each square. There are 15 squares, so the area is 15 square units!","d":"m"},{"t":"A shape is covered by 11 square units. What is its area?","o":["10 square units","12 square units","11 square units","9 square units"],"a":2,"e":"Count each square. There are 11 squares, so the area is 11 square units!","d":"m"},{"t":"What do we use to measure area?","o":["Inches","Square units","Pounds","Cups"],"a":1,"e":"We measure area by counting the square units that cover a shape!","d":"e"},{"t":"A shape is covered by 14 square units. What is its area?","o":["12 square units","13 square units","14 square units","15 square units"],"a":2,"e":"Count each square. There are 14 squares, so the area is 14 square units!","d":"m"},{"t":"A rectangle is filled with square tiles. You count 6 tiles. What is the area?","o":["5 square units","6 square units","7 square units","12 square units"],"a":1,"e":"Each tile is 1 square unit. 6 tiles = 6 square units!","d":"m"},{"t":"A shape is covered by 16 square units. What is its area?","o":["15 square units","16 square units","17 square units","14 square units"],"a":1,"e":"Count each square. There are 16 squares, so the area is 16 square units!","d":"m"},{"t":"A shape is covered by 20 square units. What is its area?","o":["18 square units","19 square units","20 square units","21 square units"],"a":2,"e":"Count each square. There are 20 squares, so the area is 20 square units!","d":"m"},{"t":"A square tile covers 1 square unit. If a shape has 13 tiles, what is its area?","o":["12 square units","13 square units","14 square units","26 square units"],"a":1,"e":"Each tile = 1 square unit. 13 tiles = 13 square units!","d":"h"},{"t":"A shape is covered by 18 square units. What is its area?","o":["17 square units","18 square units","19 square units","16 square units"],"a":1,"e":"Count each square. There are 18 squares, so the area is 18 square units!","d":"m"},{"t":"Shape A is covered by 6 square units. Shape B is covered by 9 square units. Which shape has a bigger area?","o":["Shape A","Shape B","They are the same","Cannot tell"],"a":1,"e":"9 > 6, so Shape B has a bigger area!","d":"h"},{"t":"Shape A has 10 square units. Shape B has 10 square units. What can you say about their areas?","o":["Shape A is bigger","Shape B is bigger","They have the same area","Cannot tell"],"a":2,"e":"Both shapes have 10 square units, so they have the same area! They can look different but still have equal areas.","d":"h"},{"t":"A rug covers 12 square units. A mat covers 8 square units. How many more square units does the rug cover?","o":["20 square units","3 square units","4 square units","4 square units"],"a":2,"e":"12 - 8 = 4. The rug covers 4 more square units than the mat.","d":"m"},{"t":"A rectangle is 5 squares long and 2 squares wide. What is its area?","o":["7 square units","10 square units","12 square units","3 square units"],"a":1,"e":"Count the squares: 2 rows of 5 = 10 square units!","d":"m"},{"t":"Which has a bigger area: a shape with 14 square units or a shape with 11 square units?","o":["The shape with 11","They are the same","The shape with 14","Cannot tell"],"a":2,"e":"14 > 11, so the shape with 14 square units has a bigger area!","d":"h"},{"t":"A rectangle is 3 squares long and 3 squares wide. What is its area?","o":["6 square units","9 square units","12 square units","3 square units"],"a":1,"e":"Count the squares: 3 rows of 3 = 9 square units!","d":"m"},{"t":"A garden has an area of 15 square units. A patio has an area of 9 square units. How much bigger is the garden?","o":["24 square units","6 square units","5 square units","7 square units"],"a":1,"e":"15 - 9 = 6. The garden is 6 square units bigger!","d":"h"},{"t":"A rectangle is 4 squares long and 2 squares wide. What is its area?","o":["6 square units","8 square units","10 square units","12 square units"],"a":1,"e":"Count the squares: 2 rows of 4 = 8 square units!","d":"m"},{"t":"Shape A has an area of 7 square units. Shape B has an area of ___ square units. Together they cover 13. How big is Shape B?","o":["20 square units","6 square units","7 square units","5 square units"],"a":1,"e":"13 - 7 = 6. Shape B has an area of 6 square units!","d":"h"},{"t":"A rectangle is 6 squares long and 2 squares wide. What is its area?","o":["8 square units","10 square units","12 square units","14 square units"],"a":2,"e":"Count the squares: 2 rows of 6 = 12 square units!","d":"m"},{"t":"Which has a smaller area: a shape with 5 square units or a shape with 8 square units?","o":["The shape with 8","They are equal","The shape with 5","Cannot tell"],"a":2,"e":"5 < 8, so the shape with 5 square units has a smaller area!","d":"h"},{"t":"A poster covers 16 square units. A card covers 4 square units. How many more square units does the poster cover?","o":["20 square units","12 square units","10 square units","4 square units"],"a":1,"e":"16 - 4 = 12. The poster covers 12 more square units!","d":"m"},{"t":"A rectangle is 5 squares long and 3 squares wide. What is its area?","o":["8 square units","15 square units","10 square units","16 square units"],"a":1,"e":"Count the squares: 3 rows of 5 = 15 square units!","d":"m"},{"t":"A shape has an area of ___ square units. It is 3 more than 9. What is the area?","o":["6 square units","12 square units","9 square units","3 square units"],"a":1,"e":"9 + 3 = 12. The area is 12 square units!","d":"h"},{"t":"Two shapes each have an area of 8 square units. What is the total area?","o":["8 square units","16 square units","80 square units","10 square units"],"a":1,"e":"8 + 8 = 16 square units total!","d":"m"},{"t":"A rectangle is 4 squares long and 3 squares wide. What is its area?","o":["7 square units","10 square units","12 square units","14 square units"],"a":2,"e":"Count the squares: 3 rows of 4 = 12 square units!","d":"m"},{"t":"Shape A has 11 square units. Shape B has 15 square units. Which is smaller and by how much?","o":["Shape A, by 4","Shape B, by 4","Shape A, by 26","They are equal"],"a":0,"e":"15 - 11 = 4. Shape A is smaller by 4 square units!","d":"h"},{"t":"A rectangle is 7 squares long and 2 squares wide. What is its area?","o":["9 square units","14 square units","12 square units","16 square units"],"a":1,"e":"Count the squares: 2 rows of 7 = 14 square units!","d":"m"},{"t":"A table is covered by 20 square tiles. A desk is covered by 12 square tiles. How many more tiles cover the table?","o":["32 tiles","8 tiles","10 tiles","6 tiles"],"a":1,"e":"20 - 12 = 8. The table needs 8 more tiles than the desk!","d":"h"},{"t":"A rectangle is 3 squares long and 2 squares wide. What is its area?","o":["5 square units","6 square units","8 square units","10 square units"],"a":1,"e":"Count the squares: 2 rows of 3 = 6 square units!","d":"m"},{"t":"A rectangle is 4 squares long and 3 squares wide. Tom says the area is 7 square units. What did Tom do wrong?","o":["He added 4 + 3 instead of counting all the squares","He counted correctly","He subtracted instead of adding","He multiplied wrong"],"a":0,"e":"Tom added 4 + 3 = 7. But the area is all the squares: 3 rows of 4 = 12 square units. He should count all squares, not add the sides!","d":"h"},{"t":"A rug covers 8 square units. A mat covers 5 square units. You put them side by side with no overlap. What is the total area?","o":["3 square units","13 square units","40 square units","85 square units"],"a":1,"e":"8 + 5 = 13 square units total. When shapes do not overlap, you add their areas!","d":"h"},{"t":"Sara says a rectangle that is 5 squares long and 2 squares wide has an area of 52 square units. What did she do wrong?","o":["She wrote the numbers next to each other instead of counting — the area is 10","She is correct","She subtracted wrong","She divided instead of adding"],"a":0,"e":"Sara wrote 5 and 2 together as '52.' The real area is 2 rows of 5 = 10 square units!","d":"h"},{"t":"A garden is 6 squares long and 3 squares wide. A shed covers 4 of those squares. How many uncovered squares are left?","o":["18 square units","14 square units","9 square units","22 square units"],"a":1,"e":"Garden area: 3 rows of 6 = 18 squares. Then 18 - 4 = 14 uncovered squares.","d":"h"},{"t":"Two rectangles each have an area of 8 square units. Can they have different shapes?","o":["No, they must look the same","Yes — one could be 4x2 and another 8x1","No, area means same shape","Yes, but only if they are circles"],"a":1,"e":"A 4-by-2 rectangle and an 8-by-1 rectangle both have 8 square units but look very different!","d":"m"},{"t":"A rectangle is 5 squares long and 4 squares wide. Jake says the area is 9 square units. What did Jake do wrong?","o":["He added 5 + 4 instead of counting all the squares","He is correct","He subtracted 5 - 4","He divided instead"],"a":0,"e":"Jake added 5 + 4 = 9. But the real area is 4 rows of 5 = 20 square units. He should count all the squares!","d":"h"},{"t":"A poster is 6 squares long and 2 squares wide. You cut off a piece that is 4 square units. How many square units are left?","o":["16 square units","8 square units","12 square units","4 square units"],"a":1,"e":"Poster area: 2 rows of 6 = 12 square units. 12 - 4 = 8 square units left!","d":"h"},{"t":"Shape A is 3 by 4 and Shape B is 2 by 7. Which has a bigger area?","o":["Shape A (12 square units)","Shape B (14 square units)","They are the same","Shape B (9 square units)"],"a":1,"e":"Shape A: 3 rows of 4 = 12. Shape B: 2 rows of 7 = 14. Shape B is bigger by 2 square units!","d":"h"},{"t":"Maria covers a rectangle with 15 square tiles. She says the rectangle could be 5 squares long and 3 squares wide. Is she right?","o":["Yes, 3 rows of 5 = 15","No, 5 + 3 = 8, not 15","No, it should be 15 by 1","Yes, 5 + 3 = 15"],"a":0,"e":"3 rows of 5 squares = 15 squares total. Maria is correct!","d":"h"},{"t":"A floor is 5 squares long and 5 squares wide. A table covers 6 of those squares. How many floor squares can you still see?","o":["25 square units","19 square units","11 square units","31 square units"],"a":1,"e":"Floor area: 5 rows of 5 = 25. Then 25 - 6 = 19 squares you can still see!","d":"h"},{"t":"Ben says a 3-by-3 square and a 1-by-9 rectangle have the same area. Is he correct?","o":["Yes, both have 9 square units","No, the square is bigger","No, the rectangle is bigger","You cannot compare them"],"a":0,"e":"3 x 3 = 9 and 1 x 9 = 9. Both have 9 square units! Same area, different shapes.","d":"h"},{"t":"A rectangle is 6 squares long and 3 squares wide. Lily says the area is 9. What did she do wrong?","o":["She added 6 + 3 instead of counting all squares","She is correct","She multiplied 3 x 3","She only counted one row"],"a":2,"e":"Lily got 9 by only counting 3 x 3 = one side. The full area is 3 rows of 6 = 18 square units!","d":"h"},{"t":"A wall needs 24 square tiles. You have placed 17 tiles so far. How many more do you need?","o":["41 tiles","7 tiles","8 tiles","6 tiles"],"a":1,"e":"24 - 17 = 7 more tiles needed!","d":"h"},{"t":"Shape A is 4 by 4. Shape B is 3 by 5. How many more square units does Shape A have?","o":["1 square unit","16 square units","15 square units","2 square units"],"a":0,"e":"Shape A: 4 x 4 = 16. Shape B: 3 x 5 = 15. Shape A has 1 more square unit!","d":"m"},{"t":"A rectangle has an area of 12 square units. It is 4 squares long. How many squares wide is it?","o":["3 squares","8 squares","6 squares","4 squares"],"a":0,"e":"If 4 rows make 12 total, each row has 12 / 4 = 3 squares. It is 3 squares wide!","d":"h"},{"t":"A playground has two sections. Section A is 4 by 3 and Section B is 2 by 5. What is the total area?","o":["22 square units","14 square units","24 square units","12 square units"],"a":0,"e":"Section A: 4 x 3 = 12. Section B: 2 x 5 = 10. Total: 12 + 10 = 22 square units!","d":"h"},{"t":"Noah says a rectangle that is 2 by 6 has a bigger area than a 3 by 4 rectangle. Is he right?","o":["Yes, 2 by 6 is bigger","No, they have the same area (12 square units)","No, 3 by 4 is bigger","Cannot compare them"],"a":1,"e":"2 x 6 = 12 and 3 x 4 = 12. They have the same area! Different shapes, equal areas.","d":"h"},{"t":"A rectangle has an area of 20 square units. It is 5 squares long. How many squares wide is it?","o":["15 squares","5 squares","4 squares","25 squares"],"a":2,"e":"If 5 squares long and area is 20, then width = 20 / 5 = 4 squares wide!","d":"h"},{"t":"Ava tiled a 3-by-6 rectangle but miscounted and said the area is 36. What did she likely do?","o":["She wrote 3 and 6 next to each other as 36","She added correctly","She counted every square twice","She is correct"],"a":0,"e":"Ava put 3 and 6 together to get 36. The real area is 3 rows of 6 = 18 square units!","d":"h"},{"t":"A patio is 4 by 5. You add a 2-by-5 section next to it. What is the new total area?","o":["30 square units","20 square units","10 square units","40 square units"],"a":0,"e":"Patio: 4 x 5 = 20. New section: 2 x 5 = 10. Total: 20 + 10 = 30 square units!","d":"m"}],"quiz":[{"t":"At what temperature in degrees Fahrenheit does water freeze?","o":["0","32","100","212"],"a":1,"e":"Water freezes at 32 degrees Fahrenheit."},{"t":"It is 35°F outside. What to wear?","o":["Shorts","T-shirt","Swimsuit","Heavy coat"],"a":3,"e":"35°F is very cold! Wear a heavy coat."},{"t":"2 cups is equal to how many pints?","o":["1 pint","2 pints","1 quart","1 gallon"],"a":0,"e":"2 cups = 1 pint."},{"t":"4 quarts is equal to how many gallons?","o":["2 pints","1 gallon","2 gallons","4 cups"],"a":1,"e":"4 quarts = 1 gallon."},{"t":"16 ounces is equal to how many pounds?","o":["1 pound","2 pounds","half a pound","1 gallon"],"a":0,"e":"16 ounces = 1 pound."},{"t":"Temperature went from 65°F to 78°F. How much warmer?","o":["10","12","13","15"],"a":2,"e":"78-65=13 degrees warmer."}]}],"unitQuiz":[{"t":"A pencil ends at the 7 on a ruler. How many inches long is the pencil?","o":["5 in","6 in","7 in","8 in"],"a":2,"e":"Read where it ends: 7 inches.","d":"m"},{"t":"12 inches is the same as how many feet?","o":["1 foot","2 feet","6 inches","1 yard"],"a":0,"e":"12 in=1 ft.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is the best unit to measure the length of a room?","o":["Inches","Feet","Yards","Meters"],"a":1,"e":"Feet for big distan