Fall","Very hot day"],"a":2,"e":"55°F is mild — spring or fall.","d":"h"},{"t":"How many pints are in 1 quart?","o":["1","2","3","4"],"a":1,"e":"2 pints=1 quart.","d":"e"},{"t":"Very heavy objects are best measured in which unit?","o":["Cups","Inches","Pounds","Degrees"],"a":2,"e":"Weight in pounds.","d":"e"},{"t":"The temperature went from 70°F to 55°F. How many degrees colder did it get?","o":["10°","12°","15°","20°"],"a":2,"e":"70-55=15°.","d":"h"},{"t":"How many ounces are in 1 pound?","o":["8","12","16","20"],"a":2,"e":"16 oz=1 lb.","d":"m"},{"t":"Which holds more liquid: a cup or a pint?","o":["Cup","Pint","Equal","Depends"],"a":1,"e":"2 cups=1 pint. Pint is bigger.","d":"m"},{"t":"When does the temperature on a thermometer go up?","o":["It gets colder","It gets warmer","It rains","It is dark"],"a":1,"e":"Temperature rises when it gets warmer.","d":"e"},{"t":"Light objects are best measured in which unit?","o":["Pounds","Gallons","Ounces","Feet"],"a":2,"e":"Light things in ounces.","d":"e"},{"t":"4 gallons is equal to how many quarts?","o":["4","8","12","16"],"a":3,"e":"4 gallons × 4 quarts = 16 quarts.","d":"m"},{"t":"It is snowing outside. What is the temperature most likely?","o":["50°F","75°F","32°F or below","100°F"],"a":2,"e":"Snow forms below 32°F.","d":"m"},{"t":"About how much does an apple weigh?","o":["1 ounce","1 pound","1 gallon","1 cup"],"a":1,"e":"An apple ≈ 1 pound.","d":"e"},{"t":"About how much does a pencil weigh?","o":["1 ounce","1 pound","1 ton","10 lbs"],"a":0,"e":"A pencil ≈ 1 ounce.","d":"e"},{"t":"Which of these temperatures is the coldest: 45°F, 32°F, 60°F, or 15°F?","o":["45°F","32°F","60°F","15°F"],"a":3,"e":"15°F is coldest.","d":"h"},{"t":"How many gallons are in 8 quarts?","o":["1","2","3","4"],"a":1,"e":"8÷4=2 gallons.","d":"m"},{"t":"8 pints is equal to how many quarts?","o":["2","4","6","8"],"a":1,"e":"8÷2=4 quarts.","d":"m"},{"t":"What temperature scale is used in the United States?","o":["Fahrenheit","Celsius","Kelvin","Both"],"a":0,"e":"USA uses Fahrenheit.","d":"e"},{"t":"A pencil lines up to the 7 on a ruler. How many inches long is it?","o":["5","6","7","8"],"a":2,"e":"7 inches.","d":"m"},{"t":"12 inches is the same as how many feet?","o":["1 foot","2 feet","6 inches","1 yard"],"a":0,"e":"1 foot.","d":"m"},{"t":"Which unit would you use to measure the length of a room?","o":["Inches","Feet","Yards","Meters"],"a":1,"e":"Feet.","d":"e"},{"t":"100 centimeters is equal to how many meters?","o":["1 inch","1 foot","1 meter","1 yard"],"a":2,"e":"1 meter.","d":"h"},{"t":"The short hand is on the 4 and the long hand is on the 12. What time does the clock show?","o":["12:04","4:00","4:12","12:40"],"a":1,"e":"4:00.","d":"h"},{"t":"What time does half past 3 equal?","o":["3:15","3:30","3:45","3:50"],"a":1,"e":"3:30.","d":"m"},{"t":"When the long hand points to the 6, how many minutes past the hour is it?","o":["5","15","30","45"],"a":2,"e":"30.","d":"m"},{"t":"How many minutes are in 1 hour?","o":["30","45","60","90"],"a":2,"e":"60.","d":"m"},{"t":"At what temperature in degrees Fahrenheit does water freeze?","o":["0°F","32°F","100°F","212°F"],"a":1,"e":"32°F.","d":"m"},{"t":"2 cups is equal to how many pints?","o":["1 pint","2 pints","1 quart","1 gallon"],"a":0,"e":"1 pint.","d":"m"},{"t":"A glue stick is about how many inches long?","o":["3 inches","30 inches","12 inches","50 inches"],"a":0,"e":"A glue stick is about 3 inches long. It is small enough to fit in your hand!","d":"e"},{"t":"The clock shows 4:00. What time is it?","o":["12:00","4:00","8:00","6:00"],"a":1,"e":"The short hand points to 4 and the long hand is on 12. It is 4:00!","d":"m"},{"t":"A shape is covered by 9 square units. What is its area?","o":["8 square units","9 square units","10 square units","7 square units"],"a":1,"e":"Count each square. There are 9 squares, so the area is 9 square units!","d":"m"},{"t":"A water bottle is about how many inches tall?","o":["1 inch","9 inches","50 inches","30 inches"],"a":1,"e":"A water bottle is about 9 inches tall. That is a little shorter than a ruler!","d":"e"},{"t":"The clock shows 11:00. What time is it?","o":["1:00","12:00","11:00","10:00"],"a":2,"e":"The short hand points to 11 and the long hand is on 12. It is 11:00!","d":"m"},{"t":"A shape is covered by 5 square units. What is its area?","o":["4 square units","5 square units","6 square units","3 square units"],"a":1,"e":"Count each square inside the shape. There are 5, so the area is 5 square units!","d":"m"},{"t":"A couch is about how many feet long?","o":["1 foot","7 feet","70 feet","100 feet"],"a":1,"e":"A couch is about 7 feet long. That is about as long as a bed!","d":"e"},{"t":"The clock shows 5:30. What time is it?","o":["5:00","6:00","5:30","12:30"],"a":2,"e":"The short hand is between 5 and 6. The long hand is on 6, meaning 30 minutes. It is 5:30!","d":"h"},{"t":"A shape is covered by 12 square units. What is its area?","o":["10 square units","11 square units","12 square units","13 square units"],"a":2,"e":"Count each square. There are 12, so the area is 12 square units!","d":"m"},{"t":"A notebook is about how many inches long?","o":["11 inches","1 inch","50 inches","30 inches"],"a":0,"e":"A notebook is about 11 inches long. That is almost as long as a ruler!","d":"e"},{"t":"You go to school at 8:00 in the morning. Is that AM or PM?","o":["PM","AM","Both","Neither"],"a":1,"e":"Morning time is AM! You go to school in the AM.","d":"m"},{"t":"A shape is covered by 3 square units. What is its area?","o":["2 square units","3 square units","4 square units","1 square unit"],"a":1,"e":"Count the squares. There are 3, so the area is 3 square units!","d":"m"},{"t":"A skateboard is about how many feet long?","o":["3 feet","30 feet","1 foot","10 feet"],"a":0,"e":"A skateboard is about 3 feet long. That is about the same as a baseball bat!","d":"e"},{"t":"The clock shows 7:00. What time is it?","o":["1:00","7:00","12:00","5:00"],"a":1,"e":"The short hand points to 7 and the long hand is on 12. It is 7:00!","d":"m"},{"t":"A shape is covered by 16 square units. What is its area?","o":["14 square units","15 square units","16 square units","18 square units"],"a":2,"e":"Count each square. 16 squares = 16 square units!","d":"m"},{"t":"A remote control is about how many inches long?","o":["6 inches","60 inches","1 inch","30 inches"],"a":0,"e":"A remote control is about 6 inches long. It fits in your hand!","d":"e"},{"t":"The clock shows 1:30. What time is it?","o":["1:00","6:05","1:30","12:30"],"a":2,"e":"The short hand is between 1 and 2. The long hand is on 6 = 30 minutes. It is 1:30!","d":"h"},{"t":"What do we use to measure the area of a flat shape?","o":["Inches","Square units","Pounds","Minutes"],"a":1,"e":"We measure area by counting square units that fill the shape!","d":"e"},{"t":"A stapler is about how many inches long?","o":["6 inches","60 inches","1 inch","20 inches"],"a":0,"e":"A stapler is about 6 inches long. It fits on your desk!","d":"e"},{"t":"The clock shows 10:30. What time is it?","o":["10:00","10:30","6:50","12:10"],"a":1,"e":"The short hand is between 10 and 11. Long hand on 6 = 30 minutes. It is 10:30!","d":"h"},{"t":"Would you measure a classroom door in inches or feet?","o":["Inches","Feet","Centimeters","Paper clips"],"a":1,"e":"A door is very tall! We use feet for big things.","d":"e"},{"t":"The short hand points to 3 and the long hand points to 6. What time is it?","o":["6:15","3:06","3:30","6:03"],"a":2,"e":"Short hand on 3 = hour is 3. Long hand on 6 = 30 minutes. It is 3:30!","d":"h"},{"t":"Shape A has 8 square units. Shape B has 11 square units. Which has a bigger area?","o":["Shape A","Shape B","They are the same","Cannot tell"],"a":1,"e":"11 > 8, so Shape B has a bigger area!","d":"h"},{"t":"A string is 16 inches. You need 24 inches total. How many more inches do you need?","o":["40 inches","8 inches","10 inches","6 inches"],"a":1,"e":"24 - 16 = 8. You need 8 more inches!","d":"h"},{"t":"It is 2:00 PM. Soccer is in 2 hours. What time is soccer?","o":["4:00 PM","12:00 PM","2:30 PM","3:00 PM"],"a":0,"e":"2:00 + 2 hours = 4:00 PM!","d":"m"},{"t":"A rectangle is 4 squares long and 2 squares wide. What is its area?","o":["6 square units","8 square units","10 square units","4 square units"],"a":1,"e":"Count the squares: 2 rows of 4 = 8 square units!","d":"m"},{"t":"Would you measure a caterpillar in inches or feet?","o":["Feet","Inches","Meters","Yards"],"a":1,"e":"A caterpillar is tiny! We use inches for small things.","d":"e"},{"t":"The short hand is between 9 and 10. The long hand points to 6. What time is it?","o":["6:45","10:30","9:06","9:30"],"a":3,"e":"Short hand past 9 = hour is 9. Long hand on 6 = 30 minutes. It is 9:30!","d":"h"},{"t":"A rug has 14 square units. A mat has 9 square units. How many more square units does the rug have?","o":["23 square units","5 square units","6 square units","4 square units"],"a":1,"e":"14 - 9 = 5 more square units!","d":"h"},{"t":"A wire is 11 inches. A second wire is 8 inches. How much longer is the first wire?","o":["19 inches","4 inches","3 inches","2 inches"],"a":2,"e":"11 - 8 = 3 inches longer.","d":"h"},{"t":"Which is longer: 1 foot or 15 inches?","o":["1 foot","15 inches","They are the same","Cannot tell"],"a":1,"e":"1 foot = 12 inches. 15 > 12, so 15 inches is longer!","d":"m"},{"t":"A rectangle is 5 squares long and 3 squares wide. What is its area?","o":["8 square units","15 square units","10 square units","20 square units"],"a":1,"e":"3 rows of 5 = 15 square units!","d":"m"},{"t":"It is 8:30 AM. What time will it be in 30 minutes?","o":["9:00 AM","8:00 AM","9:30 AM","8:60 AM"],"a":0,"e":"8:30 + 30 minutes = 9:00 AM!","d":"h"},{"t":"Would you measure a hallway in centimeters or meters?","o":["Centimeters","Meters","Inches","Millimeters"],"a":1,"e":"A hallway is long! We use meters for big things.","d":"e"},{"t":"Two shapes each have 7 square units. What is the total area of both shapes?","o":["7 square units","14 square units","49 square units","0 square units"],"a":1,"e":"7 + 7 = 14 square units total!","d":"m"},{"t":"A ribbon is some inches long. You need 4 more inches to reach 13 inches. How long is the ribbon?","o":["17 inches","9 inches","4 inches","8 inches"],"a":1,"e":"13 - 4 = 9 inches. The ribbon is 9 inches long!","d":"h"},{"t":"Which is later: 6:00 AM or 6:00 PM?","o":["6:00 AM","6:00 PM","They are the same","Cannot tell"],"a":1,"e":"PM is evening, which comes after AM (morning). 6:00 PM is later!","d":"h"},{"t":"A rectangle is 6 squares long and 2 squares wide. What is its area?","o":["8 square units","12 square units","10 square units","14 square units"],"a":1,"e":"2 rows of 6 = 12 square units!","d":"h"},{"t":"A pencil is 7 inches. A pen is 6 inches. How many inches are they together?","o":["1 inch","13 inches","76 inches","14 inches"],"a":1,"e":"7 + 6 = 13 inches together!","d":"h"},{"t":"Art class starts at 1:00 PM and ends at 2:00 PM. How long is art class?","o":["30 minutes","2 hours","1 hour","3 hours"],"a":2,"e":"From 1:00 to 2:00 is 1 hour!","d":"h"},{"t":"A belt is 14 inches long. You cut off 6 inches, then cut off 3 more inches. How long is it now?","o":["5 inches","8 inches","11 inches","23 inches"],"a":0,"e":"14 - 6 = 8, then 8 - 3 = 5 inches. Two steps!","d":"h"},{"t":"A piano lesson starts at 3:15 PM and lasts 45 minutes. What time does it end?","o":["3:60 PM","4:00 PM","4:15 PM","3:45 PM"],"a":1,"e":"3:15 + 45 min = 4:00 PM. There is no such thing as 3:60!","d":"h"},{"t":"A rectangle is 5 squares long and 3 squares wide. Max says the area is 8 square units. What did Max do wrong?","o":["He added 5 + 3 instead of counting all squares","He is correct","He subtracted 5 - 3","He forgot to count"],"a":0,"e":"Max added 5 + 3 = 8. But the real area is 3 rows of 5 = 15 square units!","d":"h"},{"t":"Mia says a giraffe is 18 inches tall. Is that reasonable?","o":["Yes, giraffes are small","No, a giraffe is about 18 feet tall","Yes, that is correct","No, a giraffe is 1 inch tall"],"a":1,"e":"18 inches is only 1.5 feet — that is the size of a small dog! A giraffe is about 18 feet tall.","d":"m"},{"t":"It is 11:45 AM. What time will it be in 30 minutes?","o":["11:75 AM","12:15 PM","12:15 AM","12:45 PM"],"a":1,"e":"11:45 + 15 min = 12:00, then + 15 more = 12:15. It changes from AM to PM at noon! So 12:15 PM.","d":"h"},{"t":"A patio is 4 by 3. You add a 2-by-3 section. What is the new total area?","o":["12 square units","18 square units","6 square units","24 square units"],"a":1,"e":"Patio: 4 x 3 = 12. New section: 2 x 3 = 6. Total: 12 + 6 = 18 square units!","d":"h"},{"t":"A rope is 2 feet 6 inches. How many inches is that in all?","o":["26 inches","30 inches","8 inches","24 inches"],"a":1,"e":"2 feet = 24 inches. 24 + 6 = 30 inches total!","d":"m"},{"t":"Lee left home at 7:40 AM and arrived at school at 8:10 AM. How long was his trip?","o":["30 minutes","40 minutes","1 hour 10 minutes","20 minutes"],"a":0,"e":"From 7:40 to 8:00 = 20 min. From 8:00 to 8:10 = 10 min. Total = 30 minutes!","d":"h"},{"t":"A rectangle has an area of 18 square units. It is 6 squares long. How many squares wide is it?","o":["12 squares","6 squares","3 squares","2 squares"],"a":2,"e":"If 6 squares long and area is 18, then width = 18 / 6 = 3 squares wide!","d":"h"},{"t":"Kai has 3 pieces of string: 5 inches, 8 inches, and 4 inches. He puts them together. How long is the total string?","o":["17 inches","13 inches","12 inches","20 inches"],"a":0,"e":"5 + 8 + 4 = 17 inches total!","d":"h"},{"t":"Ava says the time is 5:70 PM. What should the correct time be?","o":["5:70 PM is correct","6:10 PM","5:10 PM","7:10 PM"],"a":1,"e":"There is no :70 on a clock! 70 minutes = 1 hour 10 min. So 5:70 should be 6:10 PM.","d":"h"},{"t":"A 2-by-8 rectangle and a 4-by-4 square — which has a bigger area?","o":["The rectangle (16 square units)","The square (16 square units)","They are the same — both 16 square units","The rectangle (10 square units)"],"a":2,"e":"2 x 8 = 16 and 4 x 4 = 16. They have the same area! Different shapes, same area.","d":"h"},{"t":"Dan says a pencil is 7 feet long. What did he do wrong?","o":["He used feet instead of inches — a pencil is about 7 inches","He is correct","He should have said 7 meters","Pencils cannot be measured"],"a":0,"e":"7 feet is 84 inches — that is taller than most adults! A pencil is about 7 inches, not 7 feet.","d":"h"},{"t":"A cartoon is 25 minutes long. It starts at 4:40 PM. What time does it end?","o":["4:65 PM","5:05 PM","5:15 PM","4:55 PM"],"a":1,"e":"4:40 + 20 min = 5:00, then + 5 more = 5:05 PM.","d":"h"},{"t":"A wall is 5 by 4. You hang a picture that covers 6 square units. How many wall squares are still showing?","o":["20 square units","14 square units","26 square units","11 square units"],"a":1,"e":"Wall: 5 x 4 = 20. Then 20 - 6 = 14 squares still showing!","d":"h"},{"t":"Which is longer: 3 feet or 40 inches?","o":["3 feet","40 inches","They are the same","Cannot tell"],"a":1,"e":"3 feet = 36 inches. 40 > 36, so 40 inches is longer by 4 inches!","d":"h"},{"t":"Nina says she slept for 120 minutes. How many hours is that?","o":["1 hour","12 hours","2 hours","20 hours"],"a":2,"e":"60 minutes = 1 hour. 120 / 60 = 2 hours!","d":"h"},{"t":"A garden is 6 by 3. A flower bed covers 10 of those squares. How many garden squares are left?","o":["8 square units","28 square units","18 square units","10 square units"],"a":0,"e":"Garden: 6 x 3 = 18. Then 18 - 10 = 8 squares left!","d":"h"},{"t":"Eva has a 30-inch ribbon. She cuts it into 3 equal pieces. How long is each piece?","o":["10 inches","27 inches","15 inches","33 inches"],"a":0,"e":"30 / 3 = 10 inches per piece!","d":"h"},{"t":"Jake played outside from 4:15 PM to 5:00 PM, then did homework from 5:00 PM to 5:30 PM. How much time in all?","o":["1 hour 15 minutes","45 minutes","1 hour","1 hour 30 minutes"],"a":0,"e":"Outside: 4:15 to 5:00 = 45 min. Homework: 5:00 to 5:30 = 30 min. Total: 45 + 30 = 75 min = 1 hour 15 minutes!","d":"h"},{"t":"A pencil is 7 inches long. An eraser is 3 inches long. Laid end-to-end, how long are they together?","o":["10 inches","4 inches","21 inches","73 inches"],"a":0,"e":"Add the lengths: 7+3=10 inches total!"},{"t":"A ribbon is 48 inches long. You cut off 19 inches. How much ribbon is left?","o":["29 inches","67 inches","31 inches","38 inches"],"a":0,"e":"Subtract with regrouping: 48−19. Regroup 1 ten → 18−9=9, tens: 3−1=2. Answer: 29 inches!"}]});
